1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,120
Rituals, beliefs, and myths in this series are a work of fiction and in no regard refer to religions or faiths of any certain cultures.

2
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:15,640
Fate is woven by three forces.

3
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:16,880
Heaven.

4
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:17,800
Earth.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:18,840
Humanity.

6
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:23,200
However, the fate of some is made to be
more complicated than that.

7
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,440
I found this at home.

8
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:26,920
Do you know what it is?

9
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,280
‘Liu er mihou.’

10
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:30,440
The Six-Eared Macaque
with heavenly hearing.

11
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:35,200
You’re well aware it is
the influence of a demon.

12
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:36,840
I’m not scared of risks!

13
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:38,440
Just make sure he leaves me alone.

14
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:40,080
I’ll do whatever needs to be done!

15
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,160
Lord Warrior.

16
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:16,240
Allow me to be the one
who gives you a taste of freedom.

17
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:26,160
(Back when peace was absent
from the world,)

18
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:31,080
(the great emperor intended
to unify all the states.)

19
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:35,600
(But one rebellious warrior
refused to bow down.)

20
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,560
(He viciously fought against the emperor.)

21
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:42,200
(When the victor became the great king,)

22
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:45,320
(the vanquished was reduced
to nothing more than a rebel.)

23
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:48,800
(Thus was born a time of peace.)

24
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,720
(Although the warrior’s spirit crossed over,)

25
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:58,320
(his vengefulness and rebellious nature
lived on.)

26
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:03,880
(That feeling turned into an evil force
and grew into a powerful demon.)

27
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:10,240
(He came to be called ‘Qi Rong.’)

28
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:08,880
I invite thee back to earth.

29
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,040
You know what’s happened, don’t you?

30
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,159
But if it really is that demon,

31
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:35,760
what can we even do to stop it?

32
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,600
Its power is clearly stronger than ours.

33
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,040
But as Wu,

34
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,159
we have to try.

35
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,480
Still fancy yourself Wu?

36
00:04:51,159 --> 00:04:52,360
If you are not Wu,

37
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,000
what are you?

38
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,480
(Before all things were born,)

39
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:33,720
(the enlightened Pangu used his limitless
power to separate heaven and earth.)

40
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:36,400
(And thus yin and yang were born.)

41
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:42,440
(His breaths became winds and clouds.)

42
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:45,280
(His voice thunders and lightnings.)

43
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:51,000
(His left eye turned into the sun,
his right the moon.)

44
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,120
(His blood flowed into rivers.)

45
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:55,560
(His body formed mountains.)

46
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,640
(Though eons have passed,)

47
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:03,400
(Pangu’s infinite power remains.)

48
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:09,160
(Only one group of people are
able to connect with such power.)

49
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:12,920
(They are like the descendants
of the creator of the world.)

50
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,640
(These people are known as Wu.)

51
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,320
I’ve heard about you for a while now.

52
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,880
It’s nice to finally meet you.

53
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,920
You’re not what I expected.

54
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,120
There are no limits to human imagination.

55
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:39,280
But Wu is just an average man.

56
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:41,159
Can you really help us?

57
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:50,920
A soul binding ritual isn’t
difficult to perform.

58
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:56,880
What’s difficult is the consequences
it will have on you both.

59
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:06,360
Don’t you ever love someone that much?

60
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:09,720
Don’t you ever meet someone
and know from the first sight

61
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:13,040
that this is the person destined for you?

62
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,159
I know everyone tells us to be careful,

63
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:43,159
but we’re certain we want to spend
the rest of our lives together.

64
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,760
I’ll say it again.

65
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:51,240
I want you to think this through.

66
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:56,920
I’ll send you the details of
how this ritual will affect you via email.

67
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:57,840
Alright?

68
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:01,840
Niran.

69
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,360
How long do you plan to keep stalking me?

70
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,040
Stalk, my ass.

71
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:08,040
You sent me the location.

72
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:11,000
Because you kept bugging me
with all those calls.

73
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,000
I needed to talk to you.

74
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,240
Come on, help me out. I’m begging you.

75
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:20,280
This demon has been
ruining my life long enough.

76
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,160
Please, buddy.

77
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:24,840
Help me out.

78
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:31,840
And I’ll say this for one last time,

79
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,240
“buddy.”

80
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,080
It’s just beyond my ability.

81
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,480
Sorry about that.

82
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:40,920
Hey!

83
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,240
Wait, you jerk.

84
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:45,280
It’s “beyond your ability”?

85
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:47,000
You’re Wu.

86
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,040
I spent the whole night looking it up.

87
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,400
I know you’re Wu.

88
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,400
That’s so freaking cool, dude.

89
00:09:56,880 --> 00:10:00,280
You have the power of the god who created the world, you know!

90
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,000
Jerk.

91
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,040
That’s just a story.

92
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:04,240
People will make up and say anything.

93
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:04,760
What?

94
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:06,760
That’s not true?

95
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:07,960
How the hell could it be true?

96
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:10,880
Why don’t you use your brain just a little?

97
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,640
You gonna believe it
if someone were to tell you that

98
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:16,160
there is Mount Meru
at the center of the universe?

99
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:18,280
What’s that?

100
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:19,360
What mountain is that?

101
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,000
Whatever!

102
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:26,080
You’re still Wu.

103
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,680
Can’t you find a way to help me?

104
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:29,920
Please.

105
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:31,920
Maybe you can do it.

106
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,280
You think too highly of me.

107
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,880
And don’t freaking call me Wu.

108
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:36,600
Oh?

109
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,920
You are Wu. If I didn't call you that,
what would I call you?

110
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,600
(You are no Wu.)

111
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,080
Wu Yong Le!

112
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,360
Do you realize what you have done?

113
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,200
I was gambling.

114
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:22,760
If you were someone else,
this would have been about that.

115
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,000
But for people like us,

116
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:28,200
gambling is as good as defying heaven.

117
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:34,240
Is it right to impose on heaven
for such a miniscule trick?

118
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:37,880
So what, Gung?

119
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,640
I won, anyway.

120
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,840
Doesn’t that mean
heaven was on my side?

121
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:43,720
Arrogant!

122
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:03,080
Bear this in mind.

123
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:09,920
No one has a right to believe
heaven is on their side.

124
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,120
Heaven does not favor,

125
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,000
is no one’s friend,

126
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,920
and certainly no one’s enemy.

127
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:19,480
Heaven treats all lives equally.

128
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:22,280
Really?

129
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:25,880
But if one day I become Wu
who protects nature,

130
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:28,400
won’t heaven favor me a little?

131
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:31,480
No.

132
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,320
You are no Wu.

133
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:36,800
And you never will be.

134
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:43,200
Gung.

135
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:50,720
Gung.

136
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:54,560
Gung.

137
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:58,400
Gung.

138
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:35,520
YOU FREE?

139
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:52,120
Damn it.

140
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,680
Are you really not gonna help me at all?

141
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:58,240
Can you quit it?

142
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:00,600
Did you not understand
what I’ve been saying?

143
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:05,480
And what the hell kind of friend only
talks about himself every damn time?

144
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,200
Oh, you jerk.

145
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:07,880
Damn it.

146
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,440
You talk about yourself, then.

147
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:11,360
You ever tell me anything?

148
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:14,720
You jerk, just say what
you’re here to rant about.

149
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,160
I’m listening.

150
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:17,560
Well, go on.

151
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,280
What’s on your mind?

152
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:23,360
See?

153
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:24,720
You’re not talking.

154
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:26,760
I don’t have anything on my mind.

155
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:28,640
Wow

156
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:32,160
You dragged me out here to drink because you don’t have anything on your mind?

157
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,040
Who the hell would believe that?

158
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:40,040
I just want us to sit in silence.

159
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,120
Can you do that?

160
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:47,680
Fine.

161
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,360
Sure thing.

162
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:52,440
Whatever you want, buddy.

163
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:04,240
FEI

164
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:12,520
FEI

165
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,200
Your girlfriend?

166
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,280
My big sister.

167
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,040
You have a big sister?

168
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:21,800
Did I ever tell you I have a little sister?

169
