262
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:18,480
whether heaven still
allows me to do this or not.

263
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:22,520
Then rest assured, sir.

264
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:27,240
I’m certain everything that’s happened
is the work of an evil force,

265
00:23:27,760 --> 00:23:29,080
not the will of heaven.

266
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:06,560
(You are no Wu.)

267
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:08,720
(And you never will be.)

268
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:15,040
Did your grandfather
ever tell you about us?

269
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:22,080
Did he ever mention what your duty
will be in the future?

270
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:28,640
Gung said I am no Wu and never will be.

271
00:24:54,040 --> 00:25:00,400
You know you’re going to
the shelter, don’t you?

272
00:25:01,080 --> 00:25:02,160
Do you want to live there?

273
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:15,640
Heaven and earth may open
a path for you,

274
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:19,160
but the things that will take you there
are your own two legs.

275
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:25,320
You have a choice right now,

276
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:28,480
whether to be an orphan in a shelter,

277
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:30,680
or something more.

278
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:43,120
We will wait until noon.

279
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:45,360
Choose wisely.

280
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:13,000
(Will I ever become Wu like you, Gung?)

281
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:16,440
(You are no Wu.)

282
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:20,120
(And you never will be.)

283
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:25,640
(We will wait until noon.)

284
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:07,360
(Okay.)

285
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:08,560
(I’ll help you.)

286
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,480
(I need a hundred million, though.)

287
00:28:11,960 --> 00:28:13,840
You’re really never going to
be better, are you.

288
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:16,000
(I swore not to work for free.)

289
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:17,840
(And I have one condition.)

290
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:20,320
(My friend is joining us.)

291
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:22,160
Friend?

292
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:24,240
Since when do you have friends?

293
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:47,480
I have these in my fridge, too.

294
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:48,920
So?

295
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:50,160
Nothing.

296
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:51,560
I’m just sharing.

297
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:03,920
It looks like you had a nice childhood.

298
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:07,440
How did you turn out to be a delivery guy
who’s a gambling addict?

299
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:08,920
How’d I know that?

300
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:13,000
Maybe it’s the demon in me
that you swear you can’t deal with

301
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:14,120
that makes me this way.

302
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:16,760
How convenient.

303
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:18,200
Now you have a demon to blame.

304
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:20,480
Your life will be easier from now on.

305
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:23,600
What are you doing here?

306
00:29:24,360 --> 00:29:26,440
Did you finally find a way to help me?

307
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:30,920
A way to deal with the demon?

308
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:31,920
Nope.

309
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:34,560
But a way to make use of the demon?

310
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:37,480
I have an idea.

311
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:40,720
What’s that?

312
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:42,600
I have a job.

313
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:47,560
But I need to borrow the power
of the demon inside you.

314
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:51,760
You’ll need some training, though.

315
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:54,880
How much?

316
00:29:56,760 --> 00:29:57,080
No.

317
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,680
I’m not talking about
how much you’ll pay me.

318
00:30:00,040 --> 00:30:01,720
I’m asking how much you’re getting paid.

319
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:03,080
I want half of that.

320
00:30:03,520 --> 00:30:04,560
Otherwise, you can forget about it.

321
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,440
As you can all see,

322
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:35,640
right now, the power of evil
has taken over the minds of men,

323
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:38,000
inciting unreasonable outrages…

324
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:40,960
We don’t want a dirty money-funded
government!

325
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:41,800
Get out!

326
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:42,760
CORRUPTED GOVERNMENT, GET OUT!

327
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:45,320
Get out!

328
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:46,360
Get out!

329
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:47,160
Get out!

330
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:50,280
…and causing public unrest.

331
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:57,880
A demon of such power has not
been released in generations.

332
00:30:57,880 --> 00:31:00,400
That is why we can not waste time.

333
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:04,440
We need to find a way to seal it.

334
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:07,080
But I don’t think we should rush into it.

335
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,840
In a situation like this,

336
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:17,040
we need to think even more carefully

337
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:20,520
as to what our duty actually is.

338
00:31:21,840 --> 00:31:23,040
Our duty is—

339
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:27,360
It’s been a while since I last heard
your arrogant remarks.

340
00:31:28,320 --> 00:31:29,080
Go on.

341
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:30,520
Say it.

342
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:31,880
Hey! Yong Le!

343
00:31:33,120 --> 00:31:34,600
What we should do right now

344
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:36,480
is to do nothing.

345
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:38,600
What?

346
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:44,840
The demon was released

347
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:48,440
for political purposes.

348
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:54,600
That’s why the ones who should deal
with it are the politicians themselves.

349
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:56,440
Not us.

350
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,880
Once they come to
an agreeable negotiation,

351
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:03,320
the demon will be sealed.

352
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:07,320
Are you suggesting we do nothing

353
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:10,520
and allow bad people
to let this demon roam free

354
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:12,880
and get everything they want?

355
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:15,160
Where is righteousness in that?

356
00:32:15,760 --> 00:32:17,840
Did our ancestors and our school
teach us this?

357
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:20,480
Did they teach us to turn a blind eye
and neglect our duty?

358
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:23,360
Our ancestors gave us one duty;

359
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:26,440
to protect heaven and nature.

360
00:32:29,360 --> 00:32:30,960
Not to serve the powerful,

361
00:32:34,120 --> 00:32:35,840
nor to use our power for wealth.

362
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:40,400
That’s reasonable.

363
00:32:40,720 --> 00:32:42,200
Sira has a point.

364
00:32:43,080 --> 00:32:44,960
You two go and tell athat person,

365
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:49,320
the man you let go of your honor to serve,

366
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,920
that he has caused this problem,

367
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:54,360
and he will have to solve it on his own.

368
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:04,920
We are brothers and sisters
from the same school.

369
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:08,160
Are you heartless enough to turn us down?

370
00:33:12,360 --> 00:33:13,880
We agreed to see you

371
00:33:14,520 --> 00:33:16,080
even when you have
thoroughly destroyed our name.

372
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:18,000
That is more than generous enough.

373
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:23,800
Yo.

374
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:25,280
What did your friends say?

375
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:26,320
Friends, my ass.

376
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,560
Don’t freaking call them my friends.

377
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:32,040
Niran.

378
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:34,720
Niran.

379
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,800
Talking to them all at once
is just impossible.

380
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:39,040
Maybe we can convince them one by one.

381
00:33:39,320 --> 00:33:40,120
How nice.

382
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:41,760
Say, we’re able to convince
one person a year.

383
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:43,800
It’ll only take us 10 years
to gather everyone up.

384
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:44,560
So?

385
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:46,480
Do you have a better idea?

386
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:48,360
Trust me.

387
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:49,680
Let’s try and convince them again.

388
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:50,880
Listen to me, Fei.

389
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:55,400
I will never ask those jerks for help again!

390
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:58,520
Are you going to just give up?

391
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:04,920
Damn it.

392
00:34:05,320 --> 00:34:07,320
I thought this was my ticket to being rich.

393
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:09,719
But it’s over already?

394
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,360
What the hell are you standing there for?

395
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:20,480
Get in the damn car!

396
00:34:20,639 --> 00:34:21,760
Are we defeating this demon or not?

397
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:23,679
Hurry up!

398
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:25,760
Stop dawdling and get in here!

399
00:34:40,719 --> 00:34:41,400
What are we doing here?

400
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:43,199
We’re here looking for help.

401
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:46,880
Don’t tell me you’re here to see—

402
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:04,080
Right.

403
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:05,640
I knew it.

404
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:09,560
Bro.

405
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:12,640
Bro!

406
00:35:14,520 --> 00:35:15,080
You jerk!

407
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:17,800
It’s not me!

408
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:20,600
I didn’t do anything!

409
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:24,040
Niran!

410
00:35:34,200 --> 00:35:34,680
Here.

411
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:35,960
For while we wait.

412
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:48,160
Oh, hey.

413
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:52,320
Niran said I need to learn how to
control the demon inside me.

414
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:55,200
Do you know what I have to do exactly?

415
00:35:56,600 --> 00:36:00,040
Don’t tell me you agreed to this without knowing what you’re actually in for?

416
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:02,880
Yep.

417
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:09,920
Forget it!

418
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:10,400
Bro.

419
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:12,360
You troublemaker!

420
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:12,880
Come on.

421
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,240
Of course you never come to
see me when you’re happy!

422
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:15,400
-You listening to me?
-Always the bad things.

423
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:17,280
You’re unbelievable. In your dreams!

424
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:18,920
Damn it. He’s not listening to me at all.

425
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:20,800
Hey, don’t walk away from me.

426
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:22,360
Talk to me!

427
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:24,800
I’m not making sense to you?

428
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:26,960
It’s you who are talking nonsense! Not me!

429
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:29,080
How dare he.

430
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,400
Oh, hey.

431
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:34,360
It’s been a while.

432
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:36,120
Aren’t you a big shot now?

433
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:42,560
Who’s this guy?

434
00:36:47,520 --> 00:36:48,760
Who are you?

435
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:50,760
A friend…

436
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:54,160
I’m Niran’s business partner.

437
00:36:57,680 --> 00:36:58,720
Alright, alright, alright.

438
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:00,640
Live long and grow old together,
why don’t you?

439
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:01,880
And leave me the hell alone!

440
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:03,880
What the hell, dude.

441
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:11,600
Please.

442
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:15,480
I wouldn’t be begging for your help
if it wasn’t out of my hands.

443
00:37:16,200 --> 00:37:17,520
Stop being so carefree and help me out.

444
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:19,280
Carefree, my ass!

445
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:21,160
I’m tired.

446
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,840
I’m so freaking tired.

447
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:28,080
You can only defeat so many yao
before they keep respawning!

448
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:29,360
I’m done.

449
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:31,720
Enough is enough!

450
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:33,000
I gave up.

451
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:36,480
But this is not just yao.

452
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:39,520
It’s a powerful demon

453
00:37:40,240 --> 00:37:42,600
that is a threat to heaven and earth.

454
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:44,160
We can’t let it roam free.

455
00:37:44,480 --> 00:37:47,400
Then, go and tell your boss to resign.

456
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:48,400
That will end it.

457
00:37:48,640 --> 00:37:48,960
Damn it.

458
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:50,720
Sira said the same thing.

459
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:52,240
He’s a smart one, that.

460
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:54,200
Niran, let’s go. We’re wasting our time.

461
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:58,560
I’m at my wit’s end here, bro.

462
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,240
I’m cornered.

463
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:05,280
I don’t know what to do.

464
00:38:09,320 --> 00:38:11,200
There’s no one else I can rely on but you.

465
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:39,840
Which one is it?

466
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:41,840
Her.

467
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:46,040
We still need more people.

468
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:48,680
It is said in the ancestors’ records that

469
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:51,080
to seal a demon of Qi Rong’s magnitude,

470
00:38:51,080 --> 00:38:52,440
we need nine Wu.

471
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:53,600
No, we don’t.

472
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:55,480
I used to talk to some old masters
about this.

473
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:59,080
Defeating a demon is just like
defeating yao.

474
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:03,880
We only need one fashi as
the ritual master to defeat a demon.

475
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:07,920
The rest of the people are there
to bolster yang forces.

476
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:10,600
So it can be anyone?

477
00:39:11,440 --> 00:39:12,440
They don’t have to be Wu.

478
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:13,880
There are three of us right now.

479
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:17,800
Including this man here, we have four.

480
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:20,000
Okay.

481
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:22,040
We only need to find five more people.

482
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:29,360
That’s our fifth member.

483
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:40,360
What kind of job?

484
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:42,280
It’d better not be a pyramid scheme.

485
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:43,120
Of course not.

486
00:39:44,320 --> 00:39:45,200
This is just temporary.

487
00:39:51,120 --> 00:39:52,680
I’m gonna take you demon hunting.

488
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:53,840
What?

489
00:39:57,520 --> 00:39:59,480
Why are you laughing, jerk?

490
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:00,800
As for the last one…

491
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,640
I know someone.

492
00:40:06,080 --> 00:40:08,040
I don’t know if he’ll agree to join, though.

493
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:09,160
Hey.

494
00:40:09,720 --> 00:40:10,320
How have you been?

495
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:16,520
Are you doing fortune telling or
feng shui designing right now?

496
00:40:16,920 --> 00:40:17,400
No.

497
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:18,600
I’m done with that.

498
00:40:19,840 --> 00:40:20,240
Why?

499
00:40:22,080 --> 00:40:22,800
I’m not good at it.

500
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:23,760
So I quit.

501
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:26,880
Better leave it for people
who actually have a gift for it.

502
00:40:30,720 --> 00:40:31,960
It kind of sounds like you’re accusing me.

503
00:40:32,560 --> 00:40:33,560
I didn’t say anything.

504
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,800
My brother and I are sealing a demon.

505
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:37,640
We need your help.

506
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:45,160
I swear it’s the real deal this time.

507
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:09,720
It’s been a while, huh, kiddo!

508
00:41:10,680 --> 00:41:11,600
You busy?

509
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:12,400
I have a job for ya.

510
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:12,920
I’ll take it.

511
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:18,240
Hey, you’re allowed to ask
what the job is, you know?

512
00:41:18,640 --> 00:41:19,960
As long as you pay fair, I’ll do it.

513
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:31,600
I’ll get straight to the point.

514
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:37,280
Our goal is to seal Qi Rong
as quickly as possible.

515
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:38,560
That’s why…

516
00:41:42,760 --> 00:41:43,960
I’ll be the ritual master.

517
00:41:45,080 --> 00:41:45,760
You

518
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:47,800
and jiejie,

519
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:49,760
are my main support.

520
00:41:50,960 --> 00:41:52,560
Yok, you command the rhythm of the ritual.

521
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:55,440
You done this before?

522
00:41:56,360 --> 00:42:00,080
If by this, you mean being tricked into playing the drum for an exorcism,

523
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:01,360
then, yes.

524
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:04,880
If I told you what it was for,
would you show up for the job?

525
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:08,000
Master Tong.

526
00:42:09,240 --> 00:42:11,040
Since your expertise is
in the art of I-Ching…

527
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:13,760
I know just a little.

528
00:42:14,720 --> 00:42:15,640
You’re our scribe.

529
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:19,640
As for the three of you…

530
00:42:23,360 --> 00:42:24,760
We’ll find something for you to do.

531
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:31,320
But the most important role is you, Pete.

532
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:37,120
Since you have the Six-Eared Macaque
inside you,

533
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:40,440
this ritual can’t begin without you.

534
00:42:44,080 --> 00:42:47,280
The Six-Eared Macaque’s power is to hear everything between heaven and earth.

535
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:49,240
You have to borrow its power
to locate Qi Rong.

536
00:42:50,200 --> 00:42:56,560
The rest of us will find
the most efficient spot for the ritual.

537
00:42:58,120 --> 00:42:58,920
What do I have to do?

538
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:03,040
First, we will have to try awakening
the demon inside you.

539
00:43:03,880 --> 00:43:07,600
We’ll see how well you can control it.

540
00:43:15,520 --> 00:43:16,880
I will slowly draw the demon out.

541
00:43:18,600 --> 00:43:24,320
Your job is to do whatever it takes
to retain your awareness.

542
00:43:26,240 --> 00:43:26,800
Most importantly,

543
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:30,840
don’t let the demon devour you.

544
00:43:33,880 --> 00:43:35,400
Year of the Horse, Month of the Snake,

545
00:43:35,920 --> 00:43:38,280
Day of the Tiger, approaching
Hour of the Monkey.

546
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:40,960
The timing is… completely ominous.

547
00:45:17,680 --> 00:45:18,680
15.05.

548
00:45:19,600 --> 00:45:20,640
The fire element begins to form.

549
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:44,160
15.07.

550
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:46,160
Forces are crashing.

551
00:45:47,920 --> 00:45:48,760
You bastard!

552
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:57,920
Stop being so troublesome.

553
00:46:08,800 --> 00:46:10,200
What the fuck is wrong with you?

554
00:46:21,840 --> 00:46:22,560
Pete!

555
00:47:05,680 --> 00:47:07,920
15.17.

556
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:10,000
The demon appears.

557
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:12,400
- Shit!
- Crap!

558
00:47:18,000 --> 00:47:18,360
Pete.

559
00:47:18,840 --> 00:47:19,800
Can you hear me?

560
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:36,400
Idiot.

561
00:47:36,400 --> 00:47:37,600
Don’t puke here.

562
00:47:38,920 --> 00:47:40,040
So much for not being drunk.

563
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:40,920
Look at you.

564
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:42,920
I’m not drunk.

565
00:47:43,240 --> 00:47:44,960
I’m… calling a cab.

566
00:47:47,440 --> 00:47:50,160
Oh, crap.

567
00:47:50,600 --> 00:47:51,440
My phone’s dead.

568
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:54,440
What?

569
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:55,560
Get me a cab.

570
00:47:56,520 --> 00:47:58,520
Oh, damn it, what a burden.

571
00:48:02,720 --> 00:48:03,240
Give me your address.

572
00:48:05,600 --> 00:48:05,920
Hey.

573
00:48:08,280 --> 00:48:08,640
Pete.

574
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:09,960
Pete.

575
00:48:51,960 --> 00:48:54,360
Damn, when did I fall asleep?

576
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:56,880
You were drunk.

577
00:48:57,440 --> 00:48:58,440
You told me to get you a cab.

578
00:48:59,040 --> 00:49:02,160
But you fell asleep before you even
told me where you live.

579
00:49:03,400 --> 00:49:05,640
Well, I’m sober now.

580
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:06,680
As you should.

581
00:49:07,520 --> 00:49:08,880
You were asleep for a long time.

582
00:49:10,960 --> 00:49:14,560
I’ll… hail a cab.

583
00:49:19,880 --> 00:49:20,560
You sure you’re okay?

584
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:22,000
Yeah.

585
00:49:35,560 --> 00:49:40,120
THIS IS MY ADDRESS SO YOU CAN GET ME A CAB NEXT TIME I’M DRUNK.

586
00:49:48,400 --> 00:49:50,120
He told me it’s too risky.

587
00:49:50,240 --> 00:49:51,640
But I don’t think we have other options.

588
00:49:51,800 --> 00:49:52,520
What does that mean?

589
00:49:52,760 --> 00:49:55,440
I have to find a way to help you gain
control over the monkey inside you.

590
00:49:55,800 --> 00:49:57,040
What the hell are you doing here
first thing in the morning?

591
00:49:57,520 --> 00:49:58,440
I’m moving in.

592
00:49:58,440 --> 00:49:59,120
We’re training.

593
00:50:00,880 --> 00:50:02,360
Do I have to carry this shit?

594
00:50:02,440 --> 00:50:03,280
I told you to stay still.

595
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:03,800
Hey!

596
00:50:04,680 --> 00:50:06,040
You still have a massive weakness.

597
00:50:06,200 --> 00:50:07,200
My anger, isn’t it?

598
00:50:07,400 --> 00:50:07,680
Yes.

599
00:50:10,520 --> 00:50:13,320
Thank you for not giving up on me.
